provisions.content:
In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,—
(a)     “Assembly” means the National Assembly of Pakistan;
(b)     “Chairman” means the Chairman of the Senate;
(c)     “member” means a member of the Senate of Pakistan or the National
Assembly;
(d)     “Senate” means the Senate of Pakistan;
(e)     “session” means the period commencing on the day of the first sitting of the
Senate or the Assembly after having been summoned until the Senate or
Assembly is prorogued; and
(f)     “Speaker” means the Speaker of the National Assembly.
